WEBVTT

00:12:26.891 --> 00:12:31.018
pointed at my then 16-year-old
sister, and said,

00:12:31.043 --> 00:12:33.161
"Do you remember when you were that age?

00:12:33.201 --> 00:12:36.169
How would you have liked to grow up
without your mother?"

00:12:37.568 --> 00:12:40.199
Her oncologist was there too, and said,

00:12:40.238 --> 00:12:42.177
"This is your mother.

00:12:42.177 --> 00:12:44.830
Can you really face yourself
for the rest of your life

00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:46.607
if you don't do everything for her?"

00:12:48.375 --> 00:12:50.435
I knew my mother so well.

00:12:50.435 --> 00:12:53.595
I understood what
her directives meant so well,

00:12:53.595 --> 00:12:55.035
but I was a physician.

00:12:57.413 --> 00:13:01.884
That was the single hardest
decision I ever made,